13:30.677 --> 13:32.911
Don't worry
about Pat.

13:32.913 --> 13:34.012
Who's Pat?

13:34.014 --> 13:35.413
TODD:
Uh, he's a purveyor

13:35.415 --> 13:37.582
of ice cream, uh,
brief incarcerant...

13:37.584 --> 13:39.584
jean art enthusiast.

13:39.586 --> 13:41.519
No, he's the guy
that tried to murder us.

13:41.521 --> 13:42.687
Okay? And then
Todd ran over him

13:42.689 --> 13:44.756
with his car and then
squished out all his guts,

13:44.758 --> 13:47.091
and then somehow the guy got
his guts squished all back in.

13:47.093 --> 13:49.427
(groans)
And now he's still out there,

13:49.429 --> 13:51.362
probably pretty pissed.

13:51.364 --> 13:53.431
Look, we are gonna haul ass
out to that marina,

13:53.433 --> 13:54.833
we're gonna hop on a boat,

13:54.835 --> 13:56.601
and we're gonna
get out on the ocean.

13:56.603 --> 13:57.936
I mean, that's the only place

13:57.938 --> 14:01.139
we can be sure
there's no radioactive schnizz.

14:01.141 --> 14:02.607
Gail's right.
It's our only move.

14:02.609 --> 14:04.309
Does anyone know
how to drive a boat?

14:04.311 --> 14:06.377
(laughs) I have some experience
with, uh, boats...

14:06.379 --> 14:08.847
Does anyone else know
how to drive a boat?

14:08.849 --> 14:09.948
We are gonna be fine.

14:09.950 --> 14:11.449
We're gonna hug the shore,

14:11.451 --> 14:12.550
and we're zip down the coast

14:12.552 --> 14:14.519
to Zihuatanejo.

14:14.521 --> 14:15.920
We have got this.

14:18.224 --> 14:21.793
TANDY:<i> Come on. Let's do this</i>
<i>as quickly as possible.</i>

14:26.966 --> 14:28.066
Okay, it's clear, come on.

14:28.068 --> 14:29.801
I got gas.

14:29.803 --> 14:31.903
I-I mean-mean,
you know what I mean.
Come on, let's go.

14:31.905 --> 14:33.972
TANDY: Okay.

14:39.979 --> 14:41.346
Hey, Care Bear.

14:41.348 --> 14:43.748
I know this has
been a big day,

14:43.750 --> 14:46.050
so I set up a little oasis
for you in the house.

14:46.052 --> 14:48.753
You know, I lit some
aromatherapy candles,

14:48.755 --> 14:52.156
put on some Gregorian chants,
laid out a few butt plugs...

14:52.158 --> 14:54.993
JK, but I did do the
candles and the butt plugs.

14:55.995 --> 14:58.663
JK, it was the candles
and the chants,

14:58.665 --> 15:00.999
and that's my final answer.
(chuckles)

15:01.001 --> 15:03.167
Well, I appreciate it, Tandy,

15:03.169 --> 15:06.771
but I think I just need
to walk around a little bit.

15:06.773 --> 15:08.873
You okay?

15:08.875 --> 15:10.875
Yeah.
(chuckles)

15:10.877 --> 15:13.578
Just a lot's coming down
on this pregnant lady.

15:13.580 --> 15:16.180
Oh, come here.

15:16.182 --> 15:18.449
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you. Okay?

15:20.519 --> 15:22.287
I promise.

15:22.289 --> 15:23.888
That goes for you, too.

15:23.890 --> 15:26.791
Thanks, Tandy.

15:28.961 --> 15:31.029
(Gregorian chants playing)

15:33.465 --> 15:35.033
(Dawn crying)

15:35.035 --> 15:36.434
Why won't you eat?

15:36.436 --> 15:37.602
Testify.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.438
Can I help you, Tandy?

15:40.440 --> 15:42.807
Just checking in.

15:42.809 --> 15:44.776
Still not taking the nub, huh?

15:44.778 --> 15:46.744
(sighs)
No, not yet.

15:46.746 --> 15:49.414
Hey, do you mind if I have
a little word with her?

15:49.416 --> 15:51.683
(sighs)

15:53.652 --> 15:56.120
Hey, Dawn...

15:56.122 --> 15:59.257
just do it. Huh?

15:59.259 --> 16:01.793
Oh.

16:01.795 --> 16:03.094
Now try.

16:03.096 --> 16:04.762
Okay.
TODD:
All right, guys.

16:04.764 --> 16:06.831
We're entering Los Angeles.

16:15.641 --> 16:18.910
Quiet as a church mouse.

16:18.912 --> 16:22.180
(whispering):
Notoriously quiet mice.

16:22.182 --> 16:25.416
So, are we gonna have some
sort of plan if we do see Pat?

16:25.418 --> 16:26.951
Carol, don't worry, okay?

16:26.953 --> 16:28.586
Pat is most likely dead.

16:28.588 --> 16:30.755
And in the
one-in-a-billion chance

16:30.757 --> 16:32.323
that he's alive and in L.A.,

16:32.325 --> 16:35.259
there's, like, zero chance
that he could ever find us.

16:35.261 --> 16:36.394
(Gregorian chants playing)

16:39.698 --> 16:41.766
It's a huge city,

16:41.768 --> 16:42.934
and there's, like,
thousands of streets.

16:42.936 --> 16:44.135
So we're just gonna take

16:44.137 --> 16:45.303
all the little,
teeny, tiny streets

16:45.305 --> 16:46.604
that nobody ever goes on,

16:46.606 --> 16:49.007
and we're gonna hop on the boat,
and we're good to go.

16:49.009 --> 16:51.042
(Gregorian chants playing)

16:54.680 --> 16:56.547
We're one little RV.

16:56.549 --> 16:58.616
We're like a needle
in a haystack.

16:58.618 --> 16:59.884
I'll take it one step further.

16:59.886 --> 17:01.719
The needle is hay-colored.

17:01.721 --> 17:04.956
And the haystack
is made of needles.

17:04.958 --> 17:06.357
I'm telling you,

17:06.359 --> 17:10.762
there is no way that Pat
could ever find us. (chuckles)

17:20.639 --> 17:22.707
(ice cream truck music plays)

17:38.924 --> 17:41.359
GAIL:<i> We're clear. Let's pick</i>
<i>a boat and start loading.</i>

17:41.361 --> 17:43.594
ERICA:
<i>What's that smell?</i>

17:43.596 --> 17:45.663
Ugh! Pickles on a picnic!

17:45.665 --> 17:48.699
Uh, Carol. I-I-It's
nobody's fault.

17:48.701 --> 17:51.836
But our home. The baby's room.

17:51.838 --> 17:52.937
Aw, it's okay, hon.

17:52.939 --> 17:54.539
We're gonna help you
make another one.

17:54.541 --> 17:56.941
Yeah, Carol,
a-all those things?

17:56.943 --> 17:58.676
It's just stuff.

17:58.678 --> 18:01.212
You know, the only thing that
really matters is right here.

18:01.214 --> 18:02.914
The six of us.

18:02.916 --> 18:04.949
There are eight of us.

18:04.951 --> 18:06.284
Well, uh, you know,

18:06.286 --> 18:08.519
a gentleman never counts
himself or his wife.

18:08.521 --> 18:10.054
Maybe we should
go pick a boat.
Yes.
Yeah.

18:10.056 --> 18:12.156
TANDY:
Yes, we should.

18:16.395 --> 18:19.730
Well, here's two
solid candidates,

18:19.732 --> 18:20.898
<i>Ship Happens</i>

18:20.900 --> 18:23.568
and<i> The Sea Word.</i>

18:23.570 --> 18:25.903
MELISSA: Hey, you guys can take
whatever boat you want,

18:25.905 --> 18:28.873
but I'm taking this one.

18:28.875 --> 18:31.609
Come on.
<i>No Boats about It?</i>

18:31.611 --> 18:33.644
It's like they
didn't even try.

18:37.149 --> 18:39.617
Get out of town.

18:39.619 --> 18:42.620
Yeah. Finally got her.

18:44.389 --> 18:48.793
Hmm. Hungry little sucker.

18:48.795 --> 18:51.562
Making up for
lost time, huh?

18:51.564 --> 18:54.165
Oh, the miracle of nipples.

18:54.167 --> 18:55.900
Nature's horchata.

18:55.902 --> 18:59.804
Yeah, my mom told me it took
me a long time to latch,

18:59.806 --> 19:03.307
but once I did,
I never let go. Ask Carol.

19:03.309 --> 19:05.176
Tandy.
No, seriously, ask her.

19:05.178 --> 19:06.177
Okay, we good?

19:06.179 --> 19:07.678
Yeah, let's shove off.

19:07.680 --> 19:09.614
Okay, first, I'd like
to make a little toast.

19:09.616 --> 19:11.749
Uh, you know, I'd really
rather get going, bud.

19:11.751 --> 19:12.984
Yeah, Tandy, we don't have time.

19:12.986 --> 19:15.253
(scoffs) Americans.
Hurry up and wait.

19:15.255 --> 19:16.487
You feel me, Erica?

19:16.489 --> 19:17.655
I don't.

19:17.657 --> 19:18.689
(laughs)
Here you go, Gail.

19:18.691 --> 19:19.924
What?

19:19.926 --> 19:21.259
TANDY:
Todd, Melissa.

19:22.528 --> 19:24.929
Anyway, the word
toast comes to mind

19:24.931 --> 19:27.365
because America
is now toast to us.

19:27.367 --> 19:30.434
The cruel winds
of change and radioactivity

19:30.436 --> 19:33.337
have pushed us to sea,
and unlike Dawn,

19:33.339 --> 19:35.106
who took a while
to start sucking,

19:35.108 --> 19:37.441
this group has sucked
from the very start...

19:38.777 --> 19:41.345
...from the teat of friendship.

19:47.219 --> 19:48.486
Now, I'll keep this brief

19:48.488 --> 19:50.221
'cause I know that time
is of the essence.

19:50.223 --> 19:52.957
But, uh, I'd like to spend
five minutes per person

19:52.959 --> 19:54.725
on what each of you mean to me.

19:54.727 --> 19:56.561
Here, Todd, here's a timer.
Please don't let me go under.

19:56.563 --> 19:58.329
GAIL: Tandy!

19:58.331 --> 19:59.463
Let's go.

19:59.465 --> 20:01.866
Gail.
(groans)

20:01.868 --> 20:03.467
The moment I first heard
your Southern lilt,

20:03.469 --> 20:06.804
I thought I had died
and gone to the plantizzy.

20:06.806 --> 20:10.875
Equal parts class and sass,
the word "pert" jumps to mind.

20:15.747 --> 20:19.350
(in Australian accent):
Dawn. Australian for "baby."

20:19.352 --> 20:22.220
(chuckles) Like the first
light of the new day.

20:22.222 --> 20:23.821
Or a dishwashing detergent

20:23.823 --> 20:25.990
that cuts through grease
like a knife.

20:25.992 --> 20:31.195
But that's not a knife,
this is a baby.

20:31.197 --> 20:34.398
♪<i> Waltzing Matilda</i> ♪

20:34.400 --> 20:36.167
♪<i> Waltzing Matilda.</i> ♪
Everybody.

20:36.169 --> 20:37.935
Tandy, can we wrap this up?

20:37.937 --> 20:39.837
Of course, Melissa. I'm done.

20:39.839 --> 20:42.406
But at the same time,
I'm just getting started,

20:42.408 --> 20:44.275
because we're safe now.

20:44.277 --> 20:45.876
And when it comes
to the happiness

20:45.878 --> 20:47.545
and well-being of this group,

20:47.547 --> 20:51.015
I can 100%,
absolutely, positively,

20:51.017 --> 20:56.454
with absolutely no reservations,
assure you, positively...

20:56.955 --> 20:58.055
(all gasping)

20:58.057 --> 20:59.523
...this is only the beginning.

20:59.525 --> 21:01.325
PAT:
Of the end.

21:03.762 --> 21:05.830
Remember me?

21:07.132 --> 21:08.432
(screaming)

21:09.368 --> 21:10.701
(gunshot)

21:10.703 --> 21:12.036
